# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Leaderboard configuration
#
# Leave this UNSET for a fully local, offline, zero-setup board
# (scores stored in localStorage, per-device only).
#
# Set it to your PlayFab Title ID to enable the GLOBAL board.
# The Title ID is PUBLIC (it ships in the client bundle) — there
# is NO secret key here and NO backend of your own.
#
# Free, no paid API:
#   1. Create a free PlayFab account + Title at https://playfab.com
#   2. Copy the Title ID (e.g. "A1B2C") below
#   3. In the PlayFab Game Manager:
#        • Settings → API Features → enable
#          "Allow client to post player statistics"
#        • Create a Leaderboard/Statistic named exactly "HighScore"
#          with Aggregation Method = Maximum
#          (this is what stops players overwriting a higher score
#           with a lower one — the server keeps only the max).
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
VITE_PLAYFAB_TITLE_ID=
